Hi Anmol,

You don&#39;t need to use Java String literal escaping when adding regular 
expression settings or any other string type settings.

I am not sure if the User manual explicitly states not to use Java 
String literal escaping. However, there are a few examples in the manual 
and on the list on how to setup regex fields -- mostly related to 
canonicalization settings.

I am surprise to hear that you need to use Java String literal escaping 
when using the regex tool in the webapp. We should probably fix that or 
make an option that allows you to chose between Java regex syntax and 
Java regex syntax with String literal escaping.

Take care,
